277
00:34:01,606 --> 00:34:03,096
This door is loose.

278
00:34:08,647 --> 00:34:10,076
I'll fix it later.

279
00:34:17,188 --> 00:34:19,528
If even one creature
got in here...!

280
00:34:43,715 --> 00:34:44,945
Superb!

281
00:34:45,250 --> 00:34:49,199
I feel the ocean's power
in my very DNA.

282
00:34:50,188 --> 00:34:54,168
When this well is full,
the Era of the Ocean will begin.

283
00:34:54,859 --> 00:34:57,519
An explosion of life
to match the Cambrian Era!

284
00:34:58,029 --> 00:35:00,779
This revolting era
of Man will be over.

285
00:35:05,904 --> 00:35:07,604
Better fix this door.

286
00:36:31,556 --> 00:36:32,846
Teeth!

287
00:36:41,066 --> 00:36:43,236
I'm going back to Sosuke!

288
00:39:14,485 --> 00:39:15,445
A waterspout?

289
00:39:15,720 --> 00:39:17,680
Captain, look there!

290
00:39:21,326 --> 00:39:24,166
- Tsunami!
- Turn her into the waves!

291
00:39:26,097 --> 00:39:27,907
What's that?

292
00:39:32,704 --> 00:39:35,364
Captain!
Radio's out. the radar too!
a

293
00:39:39,444 --> 00:39:42,464
A little girl?
She must be Sosuke's age!

294
00:39:52,857 --> 00:39:54,787
- Bye-bye.
- See you tomorrow.

295
00:39:56,694 --> 00:39:59,244
- Thanks.
- Take care.

296
00:40:00,698 --> 00:40:03,417
Do you want
to wait here for Lisa?

297
00:40:03,935 --> 00:40:06,715
It's okay, I'll take the shortcut.
Goodbye.

298
00:40:07,372 --> 00:40:08,632
Goodbye.

299
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:10,680
Be careful out there.

300
00:40:53,351 --> 00:40:56,311
Sorry, Sosuke.
The power's out.

301
00:40:56,854 --> 00:40:59,573
The door wouldn't open, would it?
Was the school okay?

302
00:41:00,224 --> 00:41:03,264
Go home. Lisa.
a
We'll be fine.

303
00:41:03,828 --> 00:41:04,998
Are you sure?

304
00:41:05,563 --> 00:41:07,643
Don't worry,
we'll be just fine.

305
00:41:08,299 --> 00:41:12,749
We're spending the night anyway.
You should go while you can.

306
00:41:14,839 --> 00:41:16,769
Wait for me, Sosuke.

307
00:41:28,820 --> 00:41:29,810
Yoshie.

308
00:41:30,922 --> 00:41:35,112
Why, Sosuke.
It's so dark, I didn't see you.

309
00:41:35,827 --> 00:41:37,997
This is for you.

310
00:41:40,565 --> 00:41:43,145
My, what is it?

311
00:41:43,634 --> 00:41:45,064
One for you, Noriko.

312
00:41:45,403 --> 00:41:46,692
Thank you.

313
00:41:47,138 --> 00:41:49,188
Can't see a thing.

314
00:41:49,607 --> 00:41:52,127
This is such foolishness!

315
00:41:52,610 --> 00:41:55,220
I don’t want
to spend the night.

316
00:41:58,916 --> 00:42:03,136
- Oh good, the power's on.
- It's a goldfish!

317
00:42:03,988 --> 00:42:07,968
Maybe Sosuke's magic
made the lights go on?

318
00:42:08,726 --> 00:42:11,066
Extremely powerful...
Micro-typheoon...

319
00:42:11,562 --> 00:42:13,752
Ships should exercise
extreme caution...

320
00:42:15,500 --> 00:42:17,020
This TV is useless.

321
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:21,785
Those idiots couldn't forecast
their way out of a paper bag.

322
00:42:22,507 --> 00:42:24,257
You should go home, Sosuke.

323
00:42:25,009 --> 00:42:29,519
Your goldfish will bring us luck.
We're not afraid now.

324
00:42:38,589 --> 00:42:40,259
Here's yours, Toki.

325
00:42:44,028 --> 00:42:46,988
It's all wrinkled.
What is it?

326
00:42:47,532 --> 00:42:48,462
Like this.

327
00:42:51,169 --> 00:42:52,899
I know!
It's a Grasshopper.

328
00:42:53,271 --> 00:42:55,171
No, the Koganei Maru.

329
00:42:55,706 --> 00:42:58,696
That's your father's ship.

330
00:42:59,544 --> 00:43:01,413
Still looks like
a Grasshopper.

331
00:43:02,046 --> 00:43:05,475
We're leaving, Sosuke.
Say goodbye to everyone.

332
00:43:08,152 --> 00:43:10,052
Goodbye, everybody.

333
00:43:10,555 --> 00:43:12,395
Goodbye.

334
00:43:13,291 --> 00:43:15,431
Don't let the wind
blow you away!

335
00:43:16,794 --> 00:43:18,254
Climb over.

336
00:43:23,101 --> 00:43:24,771
The phones are out too.

337
00:43:48,659 --> 00:43:50,239
The sea is puffed up!

338
00:43:54,632 --> 00:43:56,562
Will the ships sink?

339
00:43:57,235 --> 00:44:01,335
They're safe out at sea.
I'm sure that's where Koichi is.

340
00:44:13,551 --> 00:44:16,651
- l see fish, Lisa.
- Seat belt!

341
00:44:28,032 --> 00:44:29,902
You've got to turn back!

342
00:44:30,301 --> 00:44:32,581
People are going
to the shelters.

343
00:44:33,171 --> 00:44:37,071
But there are people
at the senior center!

344
00:44:37,875 --> 00:44:41,215
They'll be alright.
They're on the leeward side.

345
00:44:42,346 --> 00:44:44,746
I've Just got to get home.

346
00:44:45,349 --> 00:44:47,489
You'd better go
around the mountain.

347
00:44:51,022 --> 00:44:52,482
Here we go, Sosuke.

348
00:44:54,125 --> 00:44:55,355
No! Stop!

349
00:44:55,660 --> 00:44:57,390
Look out for that wave!

350
00:45:02,934 --> 00:45:03,864
Here it comes!

351
00:45:04,268 --> 00:45:06,318
Run for it, Lisa!

352
00:45:46,544 --> 00:45:49,203
- The fish are following us.
- Seat belt. Sosuke!
a

353
00:46:03,361 --> 00:46:04,761
Hold on tight!

354
00:46:57,181 --> 00:46:58,701
That wave won't quit!

355
00:47:09,627 --> 00:47:12,846
A little girl fell in.
She was riding a fish.

356
00:47:18,402 --> 00:47:19,542
Where?

357
00:47:28,713 --> 00:47:29,913
The sea keeps rising.

358
00:47:30,348 --> 00:47:32,398
Where did you see her?

359
00:47:33,017 --> 00:47:35,127
Running on top of a fish.

360
00:47:35,753 --> 00:47:36,653
A fish!?

361
00:47:41,492 --> 00:47:42,542
Come on, Sosuke.

362
00:47:58,843 --> 00:48:01,683
Hang on, Sosuke!
We're almost home.

363
00:48:56,567 --> 00:48:57,617
A little girl!

364
00:48:58,035 --> 00:49:00,754
Here, you'd better
come with us.

365
00:49:01,605 --> 00:49:03,355
Stay there, Sosuke.

366
00:49:29,066 --> 00:49:30,846
Sosuke, do you know her?

367
00:49:52,523 --> 00:49:53,603
Ponyo?

368
00:49:54,692 --> 00:49:56,652
Yes. it's me!
a

369
00:49:57,261 --> 00:49:58,750
It's you!

370
00:50:00,397 --> 00:50:03,827
Ponyo’s a little girl now, Lisa!

371
00:50:15,613 --> 00:50:17,343
I made it!

372
00:50:36,066 --> 00:50:38,586
Now listen, children.

373
00:50:39,203 --> 00:50:42,192
No matter how strange
everything seems...

374
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:45,500
...we have to stay calm.

375
00:50:46,210 --> 00:50:47,350
Now be good.

376
00:50:51,248 --> 00:50:53,388
Take off your rain coat, Sosuke.

377
00:50:53,951 --> 00:50:56,201
Here Ponyo, you hold the light.

378
00:51:01,225 --> 00:51:02,975
I'll bring you a towel.

379
00:51:20,511 --> 00:51:21,531
C'mon, Ponyo!

380
00:51:24,081 --> 00:51:25,861
It smells just like you!

381
00:51:29,053 --> 00:51:29,663
Ouch!

382
00:51:29,887 --> 00:51:30,737
Ponyo!

383
00:51:35,793 --> 00:51:38,923
Gotcha!
Let's get you dried off.

384
00:51:43,467 --> 00:51:45,397
Such pretty red hair!

385
00:51:48,639 --> 00:51:49,949
But your clothes are dry...

386
00:51:50,674 --> 00:51:54,154
Ponyo was a fish.
Water doesn't make her wet.

387
00:51:58,382 --> 00:51:59,932
like this!

388
00:52:00,484 --> 00:52:03,264
All right!
Who wants a hot drink?

389
00:52:03,887 --> 00:52:05,877
Help me with the light, Ponyo.

390
00:52:06,357 --> 00:52:07,527
Coming!

391
00:52:08,258 --> 00:52:10,038
Think we'll have water?

392
00:52:10,427 --> 00:52:11,247
Sure!

393
00:52:11,562 --> 00:52:12,642
Sure!

394
00:52:15,599 --> 00:52:16,299
Water!

395
00:52:16,600 --> 00:52:18,060
Water!

396
00:52:18,936 --> 00:52:21,246
We have a tank outside.

397
00:52:23,340 --> 00:52:25,180
What about the gas?

398
00:52:25,709 --> 00:52:26,729
Presto!

399
00:52:27,211 --> 00:52:27,821
All right!

400
00:52:28,145 --> 00:52:29,015
All right!

401
00:52:29,279 --> 00:52:31,029
It's propane.

402
00:52:33,917 --> 00:52:35,467
Okay, take your seats.

403
00:52:36,520 --> 00:52:37,570
Okay!

404
00:52:37,855 --> 00:52:39,525
Over here, Ponyo.

405
00:52:45,562 --> 00:52:46,932
Sit down, like this.

406
00:52:50,300 --> 00:52:51,940
Put your stuff down.

407
00:52:54,405 --> 00:52:55,835
You need your hands.

408
00:52:56,373 --> 00:52:57,633
I have feet!

409
00:53:00,811 --> 00:53:01,921
Wow!

410
00:53:05,215 --> 00:53:06,965
What are you two doing?

411
00:53:07,451 --> 00:53:09,911
Her feet are like hands.

412
00:53:29,773 --> 00:53:31,083
There you go.

413
00:53:38,782 --> 00:53:39,982
This is the best!

414
00:54:28,365 --> 00:54:30,265
That hit the spot.

415
00:54:31,335 --> 00:54:33,915
What shall we do now?

416
00:54:34,705 --> 00:54:36,045
l want ham!

417
00:54:36,473 --> 00:54:38,403
She's crazy about ham.

418
00:54:40,144 --> 00:54:41,953
Then let's eat.

419
00:54:42,479 --> 00:54:45,029
But first let's start
the generator.

420
00:54:46,750 --> 00:54:49,560
We need electricity
to talk to Keichi.

421
00:54:50,988 --> 00:54:53,238
Koichi is my father.

422
00:54:53,690 --> 00:54:55,180
Is he a bad sorcerer?

423
00:54:55,526 --> 00:54:58,546
No, silly.
He's a ship captain.

424
00:54:59,630 --> 00:55:01,330
What about your father, Ponyo?

425
00:55:01,932 --> 00:55:04,562
Fujimoto!
He keeps me prisoner.

426
00:55:05,869 --> 00:55:07,769
l ran away.

427
00:55:09,573 --> 00:55:10,973
What about your mother?

428
00:55:11,575 --> 00:55:14,234
I love my mother!

429
00:55:15,112 --> 00:55:17,252
She's really scary.

430
00:55:17,815 --> 00:55:18,925
Sounds like Lisa.

431
00:55:24,188 --> 00:55:25,828
Can you help me, Ponyo?

432
00:55:42,072 --> 00:55:44,472
Maybe the fuel's too old?

433
00:55:45,375 --> 00:55:46,425
ls it clogged?

434
00:55:46,743 --> 00:55:47,732
Clogged.

435
00:55:48,045 --> 00:55:50,035
It's clogged there.

436
00:56:05,295 --> 00:56:06,465
Success!

437
00:56:06,930 --> 00:56:08,540
All bright!

438
00:56:10,500 --> 00:56:12,140
Wow, Ponyo!

439
00:56:30,354 --> 00:56:31,874
Antenna! Antenna!

440
00:56:32,222 --> 00:56:34,852
Did all the ships sink, Lisa?

441
00:56:36,627 --> 00:56:38,587
I can't see a single light.

442
00:56:56,747 --> 00:56:58,267
So loud!

443
00:56:58,749 --> 00:56:59,598
What's wrong?

444
00:57:00,884 --> 00:57:03,054
Even the radio
is out of whack.

445
00:57:04,554 --> 00:57:08,214
This is JA4LL...JA4LL.

446
00:57:09,026 --> 00:57:10,636
Come in, Koichi.

447
00:57:10,994 --> 00:57:14,714
It's Lisa, Sosuke and Ponyo.
We're all doing fine.

448
00:57:16,633 --> 00:57:18,593
We're going to have dinner.

449
00:57:19,369 --> 00:57:20,569
Ham!

450
00:57:29,513 --> 00:57:32,913
Ready? Careful, it's hot.

451
00:57:48,865 --> 00:57:50,064
It's not ready yet.

452
00:57:50,801 --> 00:57:52,261
It takes three minutes.

453
00:58:07,351 --> 00:58:08,751
Close your eyes!

454
00:58:09,987 --> 00:58:11,417
Not yet!

455
00:58:13,991 --> 00:58:15,661
No peeking, Ponyo.

456
00:58:19,596 --> 00:58:21,376
Okay, you can look now.

457
00:58:22,432 --> 00:58:24,361
And...presto!

458
00:58:30,974 --> 00:58:31,874
Ham!

459
00:58:32,142 --> 00:58:33,571
Good for you, Ponyo.

460
00:58:55,165 --> 00:58:56,945
Ponyo went to sleep.

461
00:59:04,441 --> 00:59:06,461
Is her home far away?

462
00:59:06,877 --> 00:59:08,627
I think it must be.

463
00:59:24,561 --> 00:59:27,021
Look Sosuke.
The sea is calmer.

464
00:59:28,398 --> 00:59:29,688
Because Ponyo's asleep?

465
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:31,610
Look over there!

466
00:59:39,609 --> 00:59:41,859
It's moving.
Someone's up there.

467
00:59:42,646 --> 00:59:44,226
People from
the senior center?

468
00:59:51,021 --> 00:59:52,011
It's gone.

469
00:59:52,289 --> 00:59:53,779
That's the peak road.

470
00:59:57,727 --> 00:59:59,477
Sosuke, stay there
with Ponyo.

471
01:00:11,074 --> 01:00:14,584
Maybe I could get through
on the mountain road.

472
01:00:17,981 --> 01:00:20,171
I'm going to the senior center.

473
01:00:20,617 --> 01:00:21,637
I'll go too.

474
01:00:23,019 --> 01:00:24,799
Stay here with Ponyo.

475
01:00:25,288 --> 01:00:28,218
I'm going too.
Let's take Ponyo with us.

476
01:00:29,359 --> 01:00:30,619
I'm going with you!

477
01:00:33,063 --> 01:00:36,373
Sosuke, our house
is a lighthouse in the starm.

478
01:00:37,033 --> 01:00:40,493
Everyone out there
is depending on us.

479
01:00:41,171 --> 01:00:42,841
Someone has to stay here.

480
01:00:44,040 --> 01:00:48,230
Lots of things are happening
that I don't understand.

481
01:00:48,945 --> 01:00:52,895
But right now I'm worried about
the people at the senior center.

482
01:00:54,184 --> 01:00:57,664
Just knowing you're
here will help me.

483
01:00:58,355 --> 01:01:00,965
Don't worry.
I promise to come back.

484
01:01:02,826 --> 01:01:03,696
Promise?

485
01:01:05,295 --> 01:01:06,465
I promise.

486
01:01:06,763 --> 01:01:08,103
You promised!

487
01:01:09,232 --> 01:01:10,632
I love you, Sosuke.

488
01:02:05,555 --> 01:02:08,484
I see the lights of the town!

489
01:02:09,159 --> 01:02:10,029
Finally...

490
01:02:10,560 --> 01:02:12,110
Now we can navigate.

491
01:02:12,529 --> 01:02:14,669
I've never seen
that town before.

492
01:02:20,737 --> 01:02:23,197
Did the storm
blow us to America?

493
01:02:41,291 --> 01:02:44,221
That's not a mountain.
And that's no harbor...

494
01:02:44,995 --> 01:02:46,134
Those are ships!

495
01:02:56,373 --> 01:02:59,063
The sea is piled up
into a mountain!

496
01:03:00,010 --> 01:03:03,790
It's a ship graveyard.
What's going on?

497
01:03:09,419 --> 01:03:10,589
We lost power!

498
01:03:10,887 --> 01:03:13,517
Heave to!
Drop the sea anchor!

499
01:03:14,024 --> 01:03:15,044
Aye-aye!

500
01:03:28,505 --> 01:03:30,055
Something is coming!

501
01:03:58,268 --> 01:03:59,818
A sea goddess!?

502
01:04:10,613 --> 01:04:11,513
The engine!

503
01:04:11,781 --> 01:04:12,770
We're saved!

504
01:04:13,049 --> 01:04:15,709
The engine started again.
It was Her!

505
01:04:16,219 --> 01:04:19,349
Protect us from harm...

506
01:04:47,083 --> 01:04:48,603
Come on, come on.

507
01:05:02,232 --> 01:05:06,572
A barrier spell!
Where did she learn this?

508
01:05:24,888 --> 01:05:27,317
Good heavens...she's human!

509
01:05:28,758 --> 01:05:31,337
Hey, watch out!
What are you doing?

510
01:05:39,736 --> 01:05:42,106
Stop! This is unsafe!

511
01:05:45,508 --> 01:05:46,707
Stop that at once!

512
01:05:54,651 --> 01:05:57,580
I'm simply trying
to save your sister.

513
01:06:03,326 --> 01:06:05,986
She's here.
She answered my call!

514
01:06:43,166 --> 01:06:46,296
- Fujimoto...
- You came, my beloved.

515
01:06:47,570 --> 01:06:49,240
Such a beautiful ocean.

516
01:06:53,276 --> 01:06:57,665
So full of magic,
like my ancient Devonian sea.

517
01:06:58,414 --> 01:07:00,754
It's Ponyo!
She tasted human blood...

518
01:07:01,217 --> 01:07:03,967
..and plundered all of my elixir.

519
01:07:05,221 --> 01:07:08,501
Ponyo...what a lovely name.

520
01:07:14,597 --> 01:07:16,147
It's all my fault.

521
01:07:17,100 --> 01:07:20,940
She's totally beyond my control.
It's complete chaos.

522
01:07:21,604 --> 01:07:23,884
She doesn't understand
what she's done.

523
01:07:24,641 --> 01:07:29,331
Now she's human, and she's
up there with her boyfriend!

524
01:07:30,847 --> 01:07:33,947
If we don't stop her,
the planet is doomed!

525
01:07:43,293 --> 01:07:45,693
No! The satellites are falling.

526
01:07:46,162 --> 01:07:48,412
Earth's gravitational field...

527
01:07:50,066 --> 01:07:51,526
Be still...

528
01:07:58,942 --> 01:08:02,342
Sosuke...that is his name, yes?

529
01:08:06,249 --> 01:08:09,618
You love your sister,
don't you?

530
01:08:13,556 --> 01:08:16,836
Listen, dear...what if Ponyo
really became human?

531
01:08:18,161 --> 01:08:19,621
Use the old magic.

532
01:08:20,029 --> 01:08:24,219
If Sosuke's love is real,
she'll lose her powers forever.

533
01:08:25,068 --> 01:08:29,018
But if it's not.
a
she'll turn to sea foam!

534
01:08:29,973 --> 01:08:33,343
That's where we all
came from, dear.
