01:15:22,284 --> 01:15:23,624
This is Ponyo.

606
01:15:24,820 --> 01:15:26,630
I was a fish before.

607
01:15:27,256 --> 01:15:28,516
A fish?

608
01:15:29,492 --> 01:15:31,162
Ponyo...that's a nice name.

609
01:15:33,729 --> 01:15:35,399
Have you seen Lisa?

610
01:15:35,831 --> 01:15:37,001
Lisa?

611
01:15:38,167 --> 01:15:39,627
She's not with you?

612
01:15:39,969 --> 01:15:41,109
She's at the center.

613
01:15:41,404 --> 01:15:42,604
The senior center...?

614
01:15:42,972 --> 01:15:44,232
This is my baby.

615
01:16:14,403 --> 01:16:16,623
Oh my, what happened?

616
01:16:22,912 --> 01:16:24,342
Is that for us?

617
01:16:38,494 --> 01:16:40,014
Give me the cup, dear.

618
01:16:45,101 --> 01:16:46,151
Thank you.

619
01:16:46,769 --> 01:16:48,289
Let's try it.

620
01:16:52,374 --> 01:16:53,834
It's delicious!

621
01:16:54,677 --> 01:16:56,347
Lisa made it.

622
01:16:57,012 --> 01:16:58,152
It's for the baby.

623
01:16:59,081 --> 01:17:03,441
Oh, I'm sorry.
He can't handle soup yet.

624
01:17:04,320 --> 01:17:07,830
But this will help me
make milk for him.

625
01:17:10,559 --> 01:17:12,549
Lisa gave me her milk too.

626
01:17:13,429 --> 01:17:16,269
Ponyo, may I have this soup?

627
01:17:16,799 --> 01:17:18,439
Sure.

628
01:17:19,135 --> 01:17:20,365
Thank you.

629
01:17:37,887 --> 01:17:40,927
People from the town.
It's like a festival.

630
01:17:41,790 --> 01:17:45,710
You there!
Do you need assistance?

631
01:17:46,729 --> 01:17:50,919
Thanks, we're okay right now!

632
01:17:52,034 --> 01:17:54,284
Then please follow us.

633
01:17:54,803 --> 01:17:57,383
We're going to
the hotel on the peak.

634
01:17:58,007 --> 01:18:00,557
Okay! Will do.

635
01:18:02,478 --> 01:18:03,738
The whole town's here.

636
01:18:04,113 --> 01:18:06,333
l hope everyone's all right.

637
01:18:06,849 --> 01:18:09,889
